---
description: Keep README and README-BOTSPEAK-EXAMPLE in sync on commit/push
alwaysApply: true
---

# README Sync Rule [ALWAYS]

[ALWAYS] user-visible chat output -> prose only
[ALWAYS] this rule applies only to README sync workflow

[ON-TRIGGER] user requests commit || push || publish || release
[ON-TRIGGER] && README.md changed in working tree || staged changes
-> ensure README-BOTSPEAK-EXAMPLE.md regenerated from current README.md before commit

[ON-TRIGGER] README.md changed && README-BOTSPEAK-EXAMPLE.md unchanged
-> STOP && warn: "README and README-BOTSPEAK-EXAMPLE are out of sync"
-> regenerate README-BOTSPEAK-EXAMPLE.md
-> continue commit/push only after both files updated

[REFERENCE] sync check:
  git status --short
  confirm README.md and README-BOTSPEAK-EXAMPLE.md move together when README content changed

[ALWAYS] if README.md unchanged -> no sync action required
